txt.en: Defeat Mordorrim cultists in Parth Daenath ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Mordorrim can be found in Parth Daenath.\n\nYou should defeat Mordorrim cultists and their leader, Agan-khô.
A bounty notice asks you to find and defeat Agan-khô, the Mordorrim cult leader in Parth Daenath.
You defeated Mordorrim cultists and their leader, Agan-khô. Perhaps this will put an end to the disappearances, although the rumours will likely persist.

The bounty notice reads:

'You have heard the rumours, of course. Men disappearing in the middle of the night, vanishing from encampments we have safely held for many years of siege? People say the Mordorrim are to blame, but if that is true, why have none managed to catch the cultists responsible?

'I am not saying it is true, but there is no question the Mordorrim conduct evil, corrupting rituals. One of their leaders seems to be Agan-khô, a dangerous user of dark magic. He needs to be slain, but be wary; we do not know the full extent of his powers. Discover them, and then put an end to him so he can never make use of them again, and you will be rewarded!'
